title: Ep170 Medical Malpractice
description: This week, the gals pull on their rubber gloves to talk about some hippocratic failures. Topics include a young life cut short by ticks (and doctors), the colorful consequences of ingesting silver, and yet one more way the US is missing the whole point. Pop open a bottle of Winc's Likelihood of Confusion Cabernet Sauvignon, get a second opinion, and tune in for Medical Malpractice. For a full list of show sponsors, visit www.wineandcrimepodcast.com/support
